description:
Recently sold: $196,000. Spacious twin home with great curb appeal in a wonderful location!  Huge, fenced-in back yard backs Rockslide Park, a large community park with many amenities, including: a picnic area, play area, softball, basketball, sliding, trails and a park shelter.

The large eat-in kitchen has ample oak cabinetry.  The kitchen appliances include a refrigerator, gas range, dishwasher, and garbage disposal.  A sizable living room, two bedrooms with ceiling fans and a full bath with newer tile surround round off the main level.

The walkout level features a roomy family room, the third bedroom and a 3/4 bath with a ceramic-tiled shower.  There is an oversized, attached garage with pull-down and a shed for lots of additional storage space.  Other appliances include a washer (newer), dryer and water softener.  The expensive updates have been done - newer roof, siding, windows, water heater, central air and garage door.

description: Recently sold: $220,000. Great one level townhouse in desirable community with a great association board, manager and neighbors.  Quiet neighborhood close to local amenities...grocery shopping, medical facilities, restaurants and more.  End unit home with everything on one level and no stairs.  Enjoy mature trees, beautiful shrubs, hydrangeas and a vinyl fence around the patio.  Home has nice neutral decor, gas fireplace in the living room, vaulted ceilings and a sheet rocked garage that is nice and handy right off of the kitchen. description:
Recently sold: $260,000. Looking for a great renter or renters to move in by January 1st, 2011-one bedroom is available immediately and two bedrooms are available as of January 1st. 

This house is in Coon Rapids right by Morris Bye Elementary on Crooked Lake Blvd and was completely remodeled in 2006-2007. Common areas would be the large kitchen and dining room, but you would get your own living room on the main floor and all of the upstairs area which includes two bedrooms and a full bathroom. There is also a fenced in yard with a deck and a two car garage so you would get one garage space as well. Full use of washer and dryer downstairs in the basement area that you would share with the other renter who has the downstairs half of the house. 

Rent is $650 for one person or $450 per person if you are a couple or two people looking to rent both bedrooms upstairs plus shared expenses for heat, electricity and cable-garbage and water are included in the rent. Lawn mowing is taken care of in the summer but you would be responsible for snow removal in the wintertime. Deposit required is one month's rent in advance and you would have to commit to at least an eight month lease. 

The current renter who you would be sharing with is a male in his mid 20's and very responsible, laid back and easy to get along with. We are looking for either an equally easy going and responsible person or two people (parent with custody of a child is great) or a couple since there are two bedrooms available. One cat is fine with an additional pet deposit and a dog will may considered acceptable on a case by case basis. A criminal background check will be performed so please be honest about anything that can be found in advance. A credit check will not be performed, but excellent rental history is needed and references will also be required and requested. 

This is a wonderful shared housing opportunity-please let me know if you are interested in a showing by calling me at 763-258-9722.

description:
Recently sold: $753,500. Living is easy in this magnificent waterfront dream home spanning over 6,000 square feet graced by 10 foot ceilings and wall-to-wall windows. This inviting home will greet you with a sweeping staircase that draws you into dramatic living spaces with impressive and unobstructed views overlooking the Mississippi River.  

     The elegant formal dining room combined with the beautiful kitchen and main level home office, with rich maple built-ins throughout, creates a perfect environment for easy family living and gracious entertaining. Family and guests can spill out to an awe-inspiring 16 x 30 foot deck from the living room, kitchen and informal dining area. Enjoy an expansive custom built African mahogany entertainment center with Bose surround sound, which can be enjoyed from the living room, kitchen and dining areas.

     The upstairs boasts 4 bedrooms with generous closets, 3 bathrooms, in-floor heating in the master bath and a large light-filled master shower with wonderful vistas of the Mississippi. Two loft areas give the ultimate space for a retreat or children?s playroom.

     The lower level walkout features a large recreation room with warm carpeting plus an inviting entertainment bar and relaxing views of the river leading to a walkout that is made for enjoying the outdoors.

     By living here, you are steps away from an endless array of waterfront activities including boating, skiing, wake boarding, fishing or just floating lazily on the recreational waters of the Mississippi. There is an extra lower level over-sized garage and expansive main level garage that provides all the room you could need for water toys and workshop spaces.

     Owning this one-of-a-kind home will charm you with extraordinary views and access to the grand Mississippi River for a fraction of the cost of many other waterfront homes, and still be just 20 minutes to downtown Minneapolis and a few minutes from quaint downtown Anoka. Coon Rapids High School is a leader and center for Biomedical Sciences and Engineering   An area park and Mercy Hospital is within 5 minutes walking distance.  Delightful shops and restaurants are just minutes away at the Riverdale Shopping Center. 
  For further inquiry please see website. www.3864-114th-Lane-NW
  NO SOLICITATION AND ONLY SERIOUS INQUIRY WITH QUALIFIED AND 
  APPROVED FINANCE. Realtors welcome with approved buyer.
